      <header class="product-header">
        <h1>The EnTrus System</h1>
        <p>
          Apparel, bracelets, and activation codes built around frequencies and guardians, with everything staying honest
          and local-first until the full House goes live.
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="system-grid">
        <article class="system-card">
          <h2>Frequency Lines</h2>
          <p>
            285 Hz (Form), 396 Hz (Protector), 528 Hz (Flow), 639 Hz (Drive), 741 Hz (Expression), 852 Hz (Seer).
            Each line maps to specific apparel and bracelet pieces in the catalog.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="system-card">
          <h2>Apparel Layers</h2>
          <p>
            Tees, hoodies, joggers, and shoes act as visible layers. Placement of sigils and phrases follows the
            standard EnTrus layout so every garment feels intentional instead of random.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="system-card">
          <h2>Bracelet Lines</h2>
          <p>
            Single-frequency bracelets and the Transfusion line act as portable anchors. Their activation cards and codes
            track how and when they are used, not just the design.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="system-card">
          <h2>Activation Codes</h2>
          <p>
            Each product has a local activation code that will later sync with QR / NFC tags. For now, those codes are
            printed on activation cards and detail pages so the structure is in place before the tech goes live.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="system-card">
          <h2>Guardians & Origin</h2>
          <p>
            Origin guardians and frequency guardians sit behind the system. Their role is to guide mood, timing,
            and perspective &mdash; never to control decisions. The Guardians page breaks this down visually.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="system-card">
          <h2>Local Integrity</h2>
          <p>
            Everything here runs from your machine: files, cart, activation cards. That keeps the work grounded until
            you decide when and how to connect it to public servers and real orders.
          </p>
        </article>
